1
00:01:04,290 --> 00:01:06,190
本人  克莱尔·黑尔·安德伍德
I, Claire Hale Underwood,

2
00:01:06,220 --> 00:01:08,280
在此庄严宣誓
do solemnly swear

3
00:01:08,490 --> 00:01:11,110
我必忠实执行
that I will faithfully execute the office

4
00:01:11,110 --> 00:01:13,510
合众国总统职务
of President of the United States...

5
00:01:13,510 --> 00:01:16,250
我真为她骄傲  这是她应得的
I'm proud of her. She deserves this.

6
00:01:16,250 --> 00:01:19,040
哪怕只能当几个星期
Even if it only lasts for a couple of weeks.

7
00:01:19,540 --> 00:01:21,260
忠于职守  竭尽全力
And will, to the best of my ability,

8
00:01:21,260 --> 00:01:23,700
恪守  维护和捍卫
preserve, protect, and defend

9
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:27,410
合众国宪法  愿上帝助我
the Constitution of the United States, so help me God.

10
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,600
恭喜你  代总统女士
Congratulations, Madam Acting President.

11
00:01:40,460 --> 00:01:43,250
{\an8}{\pos(194.2,158.85)}人人影视倾情奉献

12
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:46,300
{\an8}{\pos(93.2,101.2)}翻译   国士章鱼X

13
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:48,300
{\an8}{\pos(282.1,101.65)}翻译   咖喱味的虚寒

14
00:01:48,890 --> 00:01:50,340
{\an8}{\pos(100.5,244.55)}翻译   PiPi

15
00:01:51,310 --> 00:01:52,720
{\an8}{\pos(108.8,102.1)}翻译   杏仁斯嘉丽

16
00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:54,510
{\an8}{\pos(282.8,244.1)}翻译   吃冰棒

17
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:56,140
{\an8}{\pos(93.1,104.35)}翻译   WalkingNerd

18
00:01:56,980 --> 00:01:58,430
{\an8}{\pos(103.5,246.8)}翻译   煮粥

19
00:01:58,480 --> 00:01:59,930
{\an8}{\pos(235.3,246.8)}时间轴   壬虚浪影

20
00:02:00,690 --> 00:02:02,140
{\an8}{\pos(104.7,245.9)}时间轴   噃噃

21
00:02:02,690 --> 00:02:04,150
{\an8}{\pos(273.4,248.15)}后期   饿得慌

22
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:06,820
{\an8}{\pos(98.3,109.8)}顾问   老杜

23
00:02:07,780 --> 00:02:09,240
{\an8}{\pos(99.4,132.75)}校对   草草

24
00:02:09,740 --> 00:02:11,200
{\pos(110.4,212.85)}总监   草草

25
00:03:04,380 --> 00:03:07,380
{\pos(196,180)}纸牌屋

26
00:03:04,380 --> 00:03:07,380
{\an2}{\pos(208.1,242.25)}第五季  第六集

27
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:22,110
-感觉有什么不一样吗  -没有
- Feel different? - No.

28
00:03:22,110 --> 00:03:25,790
-骗我  -暂时而已  我只是代总统
- Liar. - It's temporary. I'm only acting.

29
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:34,790
现在你得全天候随身带着这个了
You have to now carry this with you at all times.

30
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:40,490
-密码吗  -没错  法律规定的
- The codes? - Mmm- hmm. It's the law.

31
00:03:51,140 --> 00:03:52,030
州长  我们刚刚听说
Governor, we just got word

32
00:03:52,030 --> 00:03:53,590
副总统克莱尔·安德伍德
that Vice President Claire Underwood

33
00:03:53,590 --> 00:03:55,320
已宣誓就任代总统
was sworn in as acting president.

34
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:56,440
您知道吗
Were you aware?

35
00:03:57,350 --> 00:03:58,310
我当然知道
Of course.

36
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:01,490
您有什么评论吗
Do you have any comment?

37
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,220
上帝保佑美国
God bless America.

38
00:04:04,220 --> 00:04:05,950
如果众议院周一的投票选了您
If Monday's House vote goes your way,

39
00:04:05,950 --> 00:04:08,920
-您成功当选的话  -我会赢的  相信我
- and you win the presidency... - Oh, I'll win, believe me.

40
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:10,330
您觉得这第三次投票能让您当选
You think this vote will be the charm?

41
00:04:10,330 --> 00:04:13,030
国会和全国人民心情是一样的
See, Congress is no different than the rest of the country.

42
00:04:13,030 --> 00:04:17,310
人民厌倦了这种政坛乱局和纷争
People are sick and tired of all this confusion and chaos.

43
00:04:17,530 --> 00:04:19,780
公众非常不满
The public is not happy.

44
00:04:20,050 --> 00:04:21,650
如果您当选总统
If you become president,

45
00:04:21,660 --> 00:04:24,120
克莱尔·安德伍德还会继续担任副总统吗
would Claire Underwood remain as vice president?

46
00:04:24,130 --> 00:04:26,510
如果她为国家大局着想的话  就不会
Not if she wants what's best for the country.

47
00:04:26,690 --> 00:04:29,490
可是第十二修正案有明文规定  你有的选吗
But given the Twelfth Amendment, would you have a choice?

48
00:04:31,350 --> 00:04:32,720
大家就问到这里吧
Uh, no further questions, everybody.

49
00:04:32,770 --> 00:04:34,270
州长还要和国会议员们会面
The governor's here to talk to members of Congress.

50
00:04:34,270 --> 00:04:35,840
非常感谢各位  谢谢
Thank you so much. Thank you.

51
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:37,420
谢谢  谢谢大家
Thank you. Thanks, everybody.

52
00:04:38,390 --> 00:04:40,090
-威尔  -我没事
- Will? - I'm fine.

53
00:04:42,110 --> 00:04:44,080
拉斯姆森也改立场了
And Rasmussen changed his vote.

54
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:46,210
他一直想找机会报复我
Well, he's been waiting a long time to pay me back.

55
00:04:46,210 --> 00:04:48,760
在罗德岛搞出个僵局好让他博得关注
Creating a deadlock in Rhode Island just gives him the spotlight.

56
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:51,330
-可以说服他  -会议定在今天下午
- He can be convinced. - Meeting's set for this afternoon.

57
00:04:51,330 --> 00:04:53,500
可如果说服不了他  我们就失去罗德岛了
Yes, but if we can't, we lose Rhode Island.

58
00:04:53,510 --> 00:04:56,090
他似乎是一个人  但也可能有别人支持他
He seems to be acting alone, but that could change.

59
00:04:56,090 --> 00:04:58,320
这个周末我们会取得进展的
We will make gains this weekend.

60
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:00,510
在周一投票前稳住局面
Shore things up by Monday's vote.

61
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:03,670
总统先生
Mr. President,

62
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:06,830
我们可能需要考虑另一种选项
it's possible we may need to consider the other option.

63
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,900
改期重新大选
A rescheduled election.

64
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:11,000
不  我会让拉斯姆森乖乖的
No, no, I'll get Rasmussen back in line,

65
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,040
顺便再多拉几票过来
and turn some others along the way.

66
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:16,030
我们已经为你和总统女士安排了
We've arranged sit-downs for you and Madam President

67
00:05:16,030 --> 00:05:17,790
和各小州议员的会面
with all of the small states.

68
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:19,220
莉安和我可以去雷伯恩  朗沃斯和加农
LeAnn and I can go door-to-door in Rayburn,

69
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:20,970
三栋众议院办公楼逐门拜访
Longworth and Cannon.

70
00:05:20,970 --> 00:05:23,680
除了白宫  我最喜欢这三栋楼了
Three of my favorite buildings after this one.

71
00:05:24,510 --> 00:05:25,520
什么事
What is it?

72
00:05:26,290 --> 00:05:30,380
南极洲麦克默多研究站
The McMurdo Research Facility in Antarctica.

73
00:05:30,970 --> 00:05:34,280
所有实时通讯渠道都中断下线了
All live feed communications have ceased or been disconnected.

74
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:36,910
不过我们收到了一名驻站的
However, we have been receiving texts and e-mails

75
00:05:36,910 --> 00:05:39,700
美国科考人员的短信和电邮
from an American scientist stationed there,

76
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:41,970
说有身份不明的
claiming that an unidentified

77
00:05:41,970 --> 00:05:44,530
武装人员实施了登陆占领
occupying military force has landed.

78
00:05:44,530 --> 00:05:46,420
你认为这些士兵是俄军吗
You think the soldiers are Russian?

79
00:05:47,140 --> 00:05:48,320
他这么认为
He thinks so.

80
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:52,320
他们乘坐的是无标记的科考船
They arrived via unmarked research vessels.

81
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:53,450
我们联系了莫斯科
We reached out to Moscow,

82
00:05:53,450 --> 00:05:55,940
但他们否认与此事有任何官方联系
but they're denying any official involvement.

83
00:05:55,940 --> 00:05:57,090
想不到啊
Surprise, surprise.

84
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:59,780
这就是悍然入侵
It's a brazen act of aggression.

85
00:05:59,780 --> 00:06:00,960
他这是心存侥幸
Well, it's a crime of opportunity.

86
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:04,070
佩特罗夫认为美国政府现在无暇他顾
Petrov thinks the US government has their eye off the ball.

87
00:06:04,180 --> 00:06:05,790
他想错了
Well, it doesn't.

88
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:08,900
凯茜  我们收到的最近一次通讯是什么
Cathy, what's the most recent communication we've received?

89
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:11,810
我是说  由不明力量发起的
What I'm saying is this aggression in Antarctica,

90
00:06:11,810 --> 00:06:13,000
对南极洲的入侵
by powers unknown,

91
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,670
正是总统之位一事
is a direct result of the uncertainty

92
00:06:14,670 --> 00:06:16,710
迟迟不得以解决造成的直接恶果
that our presidential situation has wrought.

93
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:19,010
沃茨众议员  国会黑人党团什么时候
Congressman Watts, since when is Antarctica a concern

94
00:06:19,010 --> 00:06:21,060
开始这么关心南极洲的事了
for the Congressional Black Caucus?

95
00:06:21,780 --> 00:06:23,170
我希望你不是在暗示
I hope you're not implying that the caucus

96
00:06:23,170 --> 00:06:25,700
黑人党团无权就国际事务发表意见
shouldn't have a voice in international affairs.

97
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:29,280
我希望你不是这个意思  谢谢你  兰迪
I hope that's not what I'm hearing. Thank you, Randy.

98
00:06:30,350 --> 00:06:32,560
我将于明天
I've called a meeting tomorrow,

99
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:34,980
召集国会黑人党团开会  在周一总统投票前
for the Congressional Black Caucus, to discuss our positions,

100
00:06:34,980 --> 00:06:38,680
讨论本党团在国内外各项议题上的立场
both foreign and domestic, before Monday's presidential vote.

101
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:41,120
您是在考虑转而支持康威吗
Are you considering shifting your support to Conway?

102
00:06:41,150 --> 00:06:42,730
我现在只能说
Well, all I can say at this time,

103
00:06:42,730 --> 00:06:44,910
最重要的是团结
that the most important thing is unity...

104
00:06:45,290 --> 00:06:48,240
以及民众对民主制度的信心
and the public's faith in the institution of democracy.

105
00:06:48,780 --> 00:06:50,160
就这样
That's all for now.

106
00:06:54,210 --> 00:06:56,810
你违反了《南极条约体系》
You are in violation of the Antarctic Treaty System.

107
00:06:56,810 --> 00:07:00,080
那是苏联1959年签订的条约
A treaty the USSR signed in 1959.

108
00:07:00,580 --> 00:07:01,350
我们已经是个新国家了
We're a new country.

109
00:07:01,350 --> 00:07:03,550
所以你承认了那是你的军队
So you're admitting they are your troops.

110
00:07:03,550 --> 00:07:05,330
我只是说我需要
I'm simply stating I need to

111
00:07:05,330 --> 00:07:08,090
解释一下由苏联签订的协议
interpret agreements signed by the Soviet Union.

112
00:07:08,090 --> 00:07:08,690
那么
In which case,

113
00:07:08,690 --> 00:07:11,620
你就是否定了几十年来的裁军进程
you'd be throwing out decades of disarmament progress.

114
00:07:11,620 --> 00:07:15,800
冷战已经结束了  代总统女士
The Cold War is over, Mrs. Acting President.

115
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:18,490
那我们也许需要重新修订条约
Well, then maybe we need to revisit the treaty.

116
00:07:18,490 --> 00:07:20,490
我对那不感兴趣
I'm not interested in revisiting a treaty.

117
00:07:20,490 --> 00:07:22,770
我只关心继续执政
I'm interested in staying in power.

118
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,250
克莱尔
And, Claire...

119
00:07:25,620 --> 00:07:28,200
如果我能这样称呼你的话
if I could be so familiar.

120
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,010
在我的国家
In my country...

121
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:33,490
一旦你上了台  就不会放权
once you're in office, you don't let go.

122
00:07:35,050 --> 00:07:37,750
-维克多  -总统先生
- Viktor. - Mr. President.

123
00:07:38,020 --> 00:07:40,950
你们美国人现在的总统可真不少
You Americans certainly have a lot of presidents these days.

124
00:07:40,950 --> 00:07:42,750
是啊  你可能觉得我们无暇他顾
Yes, you may think that we're distracted,

125
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:44,500
别骗自己了
but don't fool yourself.

126
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:47,790
无暇他顾  不不不
Distracted? No. No, no.

127
00:07:48,310 --> 00:07:50,110
分裂才对
Divided, yes.

128
00:07:50,110 --> 00:07:51,890
美国的民主制度可比你
American democracy is stronger than your

129
00:07:51,890 --> 00:07:55,070
利用这种小麻烦的可悲企图强大
sad attempt to take advantage of a bump in the road.

130
00:07:55,430 --> 00:07:58,280
弗兰西斯  我的关注范围
Oh, Francis, my eyes are on a landscape

131
00:07:58,280 --> 00:08:02,530
可远大于你们任何人的前途
that is so much bigger than any one of your roads.

132
00:08:08,230 --> 00:08:09,350
拉斯姆森议员
Well, Congressman Rasmussen,

133
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:11,020
我们只是惊讶你会
we're just surprised to see you come out

134
00:08:11,020 --> 00:08:13,300
站错边  就这样
on the wrong end of this, is all.

135
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:15,460
我知道那么多年前
I mean, I suppose it must've been hard

136
00:08:15,460 --> 00:08:17,230
丢掉了众议院多数党领袖的位子
losing the House majority leadership

137
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:18,900
一定很不好受
all those years ago,

138
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:20,260
但心怀怨愤
but there is a difference

139
00:08:20,260 --> 00:08:24,070
和背叛之间还是有区别的
between being bitter and being treasonous.

140
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:26,470
如果你是想要新的委员会席位
If it's new committee assignments you'd like,

141
00:08:26,470 --> 00:08:28,070
我们完全可以安排
we can certainly arrange that.

142
00:08:28,180 --> 00:08:29,320
已经结束了
It's over.

143
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:32,100
市场一落千丈
Markets are in free fall.

144
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:34,820
消费者信心到了历史最低点
Consumer confidence is at an all-time low.

145
00:08:34,820 --> 00:08:36,820
这是什么  装饰品  小玩意
What is this? A doodad? A doohickey?

146
00:08:36,820 --> 00:08:39,110
还是什么没用的奖品
A... pointless award?

147
00:08:39,110 --> 00:08:41,780
我有说过我讨厌没用的东西吗
Did I mention I hate useless things?

148
00:08:41,790 --> 00:08:44,460
这个国家已经在崩溃了
This nation is coming apart at the seams.

149
00:08:44,460 --> 00:08:47,400
是因为你  因为你对这个国家做的事
Because of you, because of what you've done to this country.

150
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,130
看吧
There it is.

151
00:08:48,130 --> 00:08:51,570
正义人士总喜欢感慨他们自己中层管理者的角色
How the righteous love to bemoan their role in middle management,

152
00:08:51,570 --> 00:08:55,360
而谴责那些真能影响世界的人
and condemn those who actually might have an effect on the world.

153
00:08:56,230 --> 00:08:59,820
-考虑考虑党派利益  议员  -我考虑了
- Think of the party, Congressman. - I am.

154
00:08:59,940 --> 00:09:02,060
你觉得你来这儿能怎么样  弗兰西斯
What did you think would happen when you came in here, Francis?

155
00:09:02,060 --> 00:09:03,810
你能威胁我
That you could threaten me,

156
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:07,380
告诉我不合作的话  全国委员会下一轮选举
tell me the DNC'll throw money at my primary opponent next cycle

157
00:09:07,390 --> 00:09:08,770
就把钱投给我的劲敌
if I don't play ball?

158
00:09:08,770 --> 00:09:10,920
还是说你打算奉承我
Or were you gonna flatter me?

159
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:12,440
一会儿说我是"党内长老"
"Elder of the party" this,

160
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:15,250
一会儿说我是"资深成员领头羊"
"bellwether senior member" that.

161
00:09:15,250 --> 00:09:16,770
我真有点高兴
You know, I'm somewhat delighted

162
00:09:16,770 --> 00:09:19,910
你到了这把年纪还能发展出点个性
that you developed a personality at this late date.

163
00:09:19,910 --> 00:09:22,000
但我希望你再想想
But I would ask you to rethink this.

164
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:25,920
在你职业生涯的晚期闹这样的事情
To come out this way on this thing in the twilight of your career

165
00:09:25,920 --> 00:09:28,900
只会给你的维基百科添一笔污点
will do nothing but sully your Wikipedia page.

166
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:31,320
你根本不明白  是吧
You have no idea, do you?

167
00:09:32,010 --> 00:09:34,990
你在这里没有分量了
No one hears you walking the halls of this building...

168
00:09:35,570 --> 00:09:37,040
现在没有了
not anymore.

169
00:09:40,980 --> 00:09:43,650
-你在帮谁做事  -什么
- Who are you working for? - Excuse me?

170
00:09:44,060 --> 00:09:48,220
我跟你这个软骨头共事了二十年
I served next to your jellied spine for two decades.

171
00:09:48,220 --> 00:09:50,670
你从没表现出过一点勇气
You've never shown an ounce of courage.

172
00:09:50,670 --> 00:09:53,310
你没有复仇的本事
You don't have what it takes for revenge.

173
00:09:53,310 --> 00:09:56,630
所以肯定有人给了你不少好处
So someone must have offered you something rather sweet.

174
00:09:58,480 --> 00:10:01,310
好好重新考虑两小时吧
Take all of the two hours you need to reconsider.

175
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:12,640
还有一份需要您签字
One more thing for your signature.

176
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:22,580
{\an7}{\pos(110.7,202.05)}克莱尔·安德伍德  美国代总统

177
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:26,530
{\an1}{\pos(136.2,65.25)}特许安全权限

178
00:10:27,010 --> 00:10:29,370
-放在这里就可以了  -好的
- You can leave this with me. - Of course.

179
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:40,200
{\pos(200.4,84.6)}弗兰西斯·安德伍德

180
00:10:31,870 --> 00:10:34,740
-哈维女士在等您  -请让她进来
- And Miss Harvey's waiting. - Oh, please send her in.

181
00:10:41,490 --> 00:10:43,180
我正要回雷伯恩大楼
I'm on my way back to Rayburn.

182
00:10:43,450 --> 00:10:44,970
请关上门
You close the door, please?

183
00:10:50,180 --> 00:10:52,660
重新投票我们获胜的可能性有多大
What are our chances with a revote?

184
00:10:52,660 --> 00:10:55,230
或者说  总统获胜的可能性有多大
Or, rather, what are the president's chances?

185
00:10:58,920 --> 00:11:00,000
我想知道
I want to know.

186
00:11:01,060 --> 00:11:04,550
就全部50个州而言  情况不太好
If it was in all 50 states, not good.

187
00:11:05,270 --> 00:11:08,440
他的反对率还是很高  而你依然低
His unfavorables are still high. Yours are still not.

188
00:11:09,510 --> 00:11:11,820
但他有近30年的经验  所以也不好说
But it's hard to argue with close to 30 years' experience.

189
00:11:11,820 --> 00:11:13,090
也许总统是对的
Maybe the president is right.

190
00:11:13,090 --> 00:11:15,110
或许他确实在众议院那里把握更大
Maybe he does have a better chance in the House.

191
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:17,430
别绕弯子  莉安  告诉我你怎么想的
Don't defer, LeAnn. Tell me what you think.

192
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:22,330
田纳西和俄亥俄的重投是他的最佳机会
The revote in Tennessee and Ohio is his best shot.

193
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:25,140
这对弗兰克来说是最佳
While it's what's best for Frank,

194
00:11:25,380 --> 00:11:27,260
可未必对你来说最佳
it may not be what's best for you.

195
00:11:28,850 --> 00:11:29,860
谢谢你
Thank you.

196
00:11:39,710 --> 00:11:41,190
你似乎是个通情达理的人
You seem like a reasonable man.

197
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:43,520
我懂得倾听  你是指这个吗
I know how to listen, if that's what you mean.

198
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:45,150
如果总统重获职位
If the president regains his office--

199
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:48,150
一开口就是如果怎么行  艾力克斯
"If" doesn't make for a winning opener, Alex.

200
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:50,600
我来这里是因为我觉得他能赢
I'm here because I think he can win.

201
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:53,720
我和他之间经常会有分歧
We often don't see eye to eye, he and I.

202
00:11:53,770 --> 00:11:56,550
但我们还是可以共事的
And yet, there are ways we can work together.

203
00:11:58,590 --> 00:12:01,530
好吧  委员会那里可能是我错了
Okay, maybe I made a mistake with the committee.

204
00:12:01,670 --> 00:12:03,060
我有时候会有些自以为是
I can be self-righteous.

205
00:12:03,060 --> 00:12:04,980
我是想清理党派  我们的党派
I'm trying to clean up the party. Our party.

206
00:12:04,980 --> 00:12:06,880
结果我说错话了
And I end up speaking out of turn.

207
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:09,670
少来"不怪你是我的错"这一套了
It's enough with the, "It's me, not you."

208
00:12:10,460 --> 00:12:11,780
你到底能做什么  艾力克斯
What can you deliver, Alex?

209
00:12:11,780 --> 00:12:13,070
我可以不碍事
I can get out of the way.

210
00:12:13,230 --> 00:12:16,230
这话太含糊  而且不够
Well, that sounds vague and inadequate.

211
00:12:18,650 --> 00:12:21,460
我想知道泰瑞·乌麦克和黑人党团是怎么回事
I want to know what's up with Terry Womack and the Black Caucus.

212
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,830
总统和乌麦克议员
The president and Congressman Womack,

213
00:12:23,830 --> 00:12:24,970
他们关系很好
they have a good relationship.

214
00:12:24,970 --> 00:12:28,650
当然了  但我可不想看到泰瑞让你们失望
I'm sure they do. But I would hate to see Terry let you down.

215
00:12:31,220 --> 00:12:35,360
如果失去了乌麦克和黑人党团  我们周一就完了
If we lose Womack and the Black Caucus, we're done on Monday.

216
00:12:35,870 --> 00:12:37,740
有几个新人我可以搭上关系
There are a few freshmen I could reach out to.

217
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:39,970
他们或许能让黑人党团同心
They might help keep the CBC together.

218
00:12:42,060 --> 00:12:43,870
你想当少数党党鞭
You wanna be minority whip.

219
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:45,390
如果我够格
Only if I deserve to be.

220
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,040
我准备回去了
I'm trying to get back.

221
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:51,610
刘易斯议员又迟到了二十分钟
Congressman Lewis is 20 minutes late as usual.

222
00:12:51,510 --> 00:12:56,890
{\an7}{\pos(204,43.2)}发信人: 旧友/新敌
我警告过你  叫走那些狗  否则还会继续

223
00:12:52,180 --> 00:12:54,570
能让他进金融服务委员会吗
Is there a spot for him on financial services?

224
00:13:00,060 --> 00:13:05,230
{\an8}{\pos(228,122.85)}警察内部备忘录早已断定商店爆炸系因燃气泄漏后
联调局才被召来  新证据显示"袭击"系捏造

225
00:13:04,990 --> 00:13:07,760
道格  待着别动
Doug, stay where you are.

226
00:13:09,340 --> 00:13:11,810
你不是说你让中情局别插手了吗
I thought you said you were telling the CIA to stand down.

227
00:13:11,810 --> 00:13:12,640
是啊
I did.

228
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:15,210
你保证过麦卡伦会老实的
So, contrary to your assurances that Macallan would behave,

229
00:13:15,210 --> 00:13:16,340
现在却出现消息泄露
we're now dealing with a leak.

230
00:13:16,340 --> 00:13:19,140
-他不想惹麻烦  -你怎么知道他想要什么
- He doesn't want trouble. - How do you know what he wants?

231
00:13:20,490 --> 00:13:22,310
你去找到他  带过来
You find him and you get him here.

232
00:13:22,310 --> 00:13:23,750
只要他知道我们让步了
As soon as he knows we've backed off,

233
00:13:23,750 --> 00:13:26,060
他就会消失的  我保证
he will disappear. I promise.

234
00:13:26,150 --> 00:13:28,550
不  你的保证对我毫无意义
No, that word means nothing to me.

235
00:13:31,170 --> 00:13:35,800
{\pos(226.8,74.7)}警察内部备忘录早已断定商店爆炸系因燃气泄漏后
联调局才被召来  新证据显示"袭击"系捏造

236
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:38,630
你写好声明了吗
You have a statement?

237
00:13:38,630 --> 00:13:41,300
还会不会有其他重大的
You anticipate any other big WikiLeaks info dumps

238
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:42,580
维基解密事件
coming down the pike?

239
00:13:42,580 --> 00:13:44,270
-你会知道的  -等我需要知道的时候
- You'll know-- - When I need to know.

240
00:13:44,780 --> 00:13:45,870
我知道
I know.

241
00:13:45,930 --> 00:13:48,230
也就是上了CNN的时候吧
Which is apparently whenever it hits CNN.

242
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:51,620
联调局之前高度戒备  他们调查每个威胁
FBI was on high alert. They investigated every threat.

243
00:13:51,710 --> 00:13:52,640
冷静
Calm down.

244
00:13:53,570 --> 00:13:56,990
我很冷静  道格  民众不冷静
I am calm, Doug. The public's not calm.

245
00:13:57,630 --> 00:14:00,580
每次失足都被强调  放大
Every misstep is highlighted and heightened.

246
00:14:00,870 --> 00:14:03,420
他们想知道选举到底怎么回事
They wanna know what happened with their election.

247
00:14:03,420 --> 00:14:04,600
我们正在解决
We're fixing it.

248
00:14:04,730 --> 00:14:07,660
他们怕的就是这个
That's what they're afraid of.

249
00:14:08,550 --> 00:14:11,700
声明是关于联调局的  大家都信任联调局
The statement's about the FBI. Everybody trusts the FBI.

250
00:14:18,180 --> 00:14:19,790
丽萨·威廉姆斯是谁
Hey, who's Lisa Williams?

251
00:14:22,060 --> 00:14:24,890
我不知道  怎么了
I don't know. Why?

252
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:26,600
《先驱报》有人打电话来
Somebody from the Herald called.

253
00:14:26,950 --> 00:14:28,370
问你认不认识她
They were just wondering if you knew her.

254
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,330
不认识
I don't.

255
00:14:40,300 --> 00:14:42,070
我需要五分钟审阅
I need five minutes with this.

256
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,960
-给你关门吗  -关
- Open or closed? - Closed.

257
00:15:06,690 --> 00:15:08,120
我那份声明怎么样
Am I good with that statement?

258
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:10,000
我做好标记了  在我桌子上
I marked it up. It's on my desk.

259
00:15:46,060 --> 00:15:48,890
{\pos(197.4,116.55)}安东尼·莫雷蒂  2次通话

260
00:15:56,820 --> 00:15:58,350
把选举交回给各州
Throwing the election back to the states,

261
00:15:58,350 --> 00:15:59,880
让我们的把握变小了
it gives us less certainty.

262
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:02,390
我觉得周一之前我们没法办妥
I don't think we can get it done by Monday.

263
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:03,960
我们都已经忙了几周了  弗兰西斯
We've been working at it for weeks, Francis.

264
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:05,570
克莱尔  别因为当职而变得小心翼翼
Claire, don't let the office make you careful.

265
00:16:05,570 --> 00:16:07,370
国会从来没让我失望过
The halls of Congress have never failed me.

266
00:16:07,370 --> 00:16:08,780
是  但那些职业政客
Yes, but the career politicians,

267
00:16:08,780 --> 00:16:10,890
他们从没这么步调一致过
they are more entrenched than ever.

268
00:16:11,150 --> 00:16:14,010
现在有了新众议院  里面的人你不认识
There's a new House, with members you don't know.

269
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,520
我们得把重点
We need to move the playing field

270
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:17,360
放回到人民的期望上
back to the imaginations of the people.

271
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:20,440
你这么相信田纳西和俄亥俄的选民吗
You have that much faith in the voters in Tennessee and Ohio?

272
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:23,360
他们会选你的  我确定
They're going to choose you. I just know it.

273
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:26,340
好吧
All right.

274
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:29,870
安排会议  我会听他们说的  你赢了
Set up a meeting. I'll hear them all out. You win.

275
00:16:30,550 --> 00:16:33,260
是我们  是我们赢了
Both of us. Both of us.

276
00:16:34,650 --> 00:16:35,510
晚上好
Good evening.

277
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:36,850
艾瑞克
Eric.

278
00:16:38,420 --> 00:16:39,710
就像是在外面吧
Feel like you're outside?

279
00:16:40,090 --> 00:16:42,010
你不是应该限制在三十分钟之内吗
Aren't you supposed to limit it to 30 minutes?

280
00:16:42,010 --> 00:16:44,510
-天啊  可别  -把健身调整好就不必
- Oh, God, Jesus, no. - Not if you calibrate the workout.

281
00:16:44,510 --> 00:16:45,850
我没事
Oh, I'm feeling fine.

282
00:16:46,090 --> 00:16:47,880
你要听从你的身体
It's all about listening to your body.

283
00:16:48,020 --> 00:16:49,660
它会告诉你什么时候该休息
It'll tell you when it's time to rest.

284
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:53,790
你有时也该听医生的  弗兰西斯
You should listen to the doctors some of the time, Francis.

285
00:17:01,490 --> 00:17:03,520
我确定安德伍德夫妇很担心
I know the Underwoods were worried.

286
00:17:03,630 --> 00:17:05,150
因为他们愿意做交易
Because they were ready to deal.

287
00:17:06,270 --> 00:17:07,320
跟我做交易
To deal with me.

288
00:17:08,170 --> 00:17:10,950
-你能肯定吗  -非常肯定
- You're sure it's for real? - Sure as I can be.

289
00:17:12,630 --> 00:17:14,800
好  再联系
Okay, we'll be in touch.

290
00:17:15,250 --> 00:17:16,080
好
Okay.

291
00:17:20,650 --> 00:17:21,770
给他打回去
So call him back.

292
00:17:23,570 --> 00:17:25,770
成功让几个民主党人改主意了
Making progress on a couple of Dems.

293
00:17:25,860 --> 00:17:27,880
阿尔斯波议员也要回心转意了
Think Congressman Alspaugh is about to turn.

294
00:17:28,050 --> 00:17:29,370
我们周日见他
We'll see him on Sunday.

295
00:17:31,710 --> 00:17:33,060
为什么要等
Why wait?

296
00:17:35,180 --> 00:17:38,650
我们明天得和国会黑人党团见面
We need to meet with the Congressional Black Caucus. Tomorrow.

297
00:17:38,980 --> 00:17:40,580
他们是安德伍德的
They're in Underwood's pocket.

298
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:44,950
是啊  能让我们说句话吗  各位
Yeah. Can you give us a second, everybody?

299
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:46,410
好的
Uh, sure.

300
00:17:46,410 --> 00:17:47,260
走吧
Come on.

301
00:17:49,930 --> 00:17:50,770
谢谢
Thank you.

302
00:17:58,480 --> 00:18:00,360
我刚得到内部消息
I just got word from somebody inside.

303
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:03,150
乌麦克在失去对党团的控制
Womack is losing control of the caucus.

304
00:18:05,180 --> 00:18:06,740
要是你能拿下他们  周一就赢了
If you win them, you win Monday.

305
00:18:08,230 --> 00:18:09,140
我们应该试试
We should try.

306
00:18:09,820 --> 00:18:11,620
好吧  我们试试吧
All right, fine. Let's do it.

307
00:18:13,570 --> 00:18:15,980
-我去安排  -今晚结束了吗
- I'll set it up. - Are we done here tonight?

308
00:18:15,980 --> 00:18:17,510
你还得打几个电话
You still have a few calls.

309
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:20,890
马克  我在想我们是不是能
Mark, I was thinking, maybe we could, um...

310
00:18:21,380 --> 00:18:23,670
取消明晚在费城的活动
cancel tomorrow night in Philadelphia.

311
00:18:24,470 --> 00:18:27,890
一趟出行和活动都不能取消  不应该取消
We can't cancel any trip, or any event. We shouldn't.

312
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:32,130
让我们稍稍歇歇会大有好处的
A second to catch our breath would be really helpful, I think.

313
00:18:32,230 --> 00:18:35,400
就得这样  汉娜  需要的话你就休息一下吧
This is what it is, Hannah. If you need to take a break, you can.

314
00:18:35,770 --> 00:18:38,310
亲爱的  我们一整周都没睡了
Darling, we haven't slept all week.

315
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:40,480
你累坏了
You're exhausted.

316
00:18:48,330 --> 00:18:51,790
-我  只是说说  -下一个打给谁
- I... Just an idea. - What's my next call?

317
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:07,320
但你不快乐
But you're not enjoying yourself.

318
00:19:08,420 --> 00:19:10,280
因为他不肯听我的
Because he won't listen to me.

319
00:19:10,730 --> 00:19:12,460
众议院他赢不了
He can't win in the House.

320
00:19:12,660 --> 00:19:15,950
我说的不是他  我说的是你
I'm not talking about him. I'm talking about you.

321
00:19:18,760 --> 00:19:21,250
我快不快乐又有什么区别呢
What difference does it make whether I'm enjoying myself or not?

322
00:19:21,250 --> 00:19:22,840
这不才是最重要的吗
Isn't that what this is all about?

323
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:29,010
你就不能...先体验它一下吗
Can't you just... live in it for a second?

324
00:19:29,230 --> 00:19:31,200
你现在掌权了
You are in charge.

325
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:32,780
-对  但是  -过来
- Yes, but-- - Come here.

326
00:19:34,810 --> 00:19:35,630
过来
Come.

327
00:19:42,190 --> 00:19:43,980
等你明早醒来
You could wake up tomorrow...

328
00:19:45,150 --> 00:19:46,280
你可以
and...

329
00:19:47,550 --> 00:19:50,690
比如  喂孩子们吃饭
I don't know, feed the children...

330
00:19:51,930 --> 00:19:52,730
挑起战争
start a war...

331
00:19:52,730 --> 00:19:54,100
你知道吗  我很抱歉
You know what? I'm sorry.

332
00:19:55,710 --> 00:19:57,960
我不应该把我想的都说出来
I shouldn't think out loud, that's all.

333
00:20:00,510 --> 00:20:01,530
不  你说得对
No, you're right.

334
00:20:01,710 --> 00:20:04,840
我们别谈这房间外发生的事了
Let's not talk about anything that happens outside of this room.

335
00:22:20,290 --> 00:22:23,400
制裁的目标是俄罗斯的寡头阶层
The sanctions are meant to target the oligarch class in Russia.

336
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:25,040
我和佩特罗夫总统谈判之前
And the more members we have on board

337
00:22:25,040 --> 00:22:27,030
我们能争取到越多成员的支持
before I sit down with President Petrov,

338
00:22:27,030 --> 00:22:29,800
这问题就能越快得到解决
the quicker this will resolve itself.

339
00:22:30,940 --> 00:22:34,510
已经在做了  我们准备出售一些战略储备
We are. We are prepared to release some of our strategic reserves

340
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:36,020
以平稳油价
to keep prices down.

341
00:22:36,930 --> 00:22:40,360
联系卡斯皮大使  再给我争取15分钟
Contact Ambassador Caspi and buy me 15 more minutes.

342
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:45,260
别把这当成是和安德伍德夫妇的交易
Uh, please don't think of this as a deal with the Underwoods.

343
00:22:46,130 --> 00:22:48,570
说实在的  他们可能周一就走了
To be frank, they could be gone by Monday.

