and conspiracy theorist on the Internet.

701
00:42:47,870 --> 00:42:51,000
一开始  格雷森说对她的名字没印象
At first, Grayson said her name didn't ring a bell,

702
00:42:51,200 --> 00:42:52,600
然后他突然联系我
but then he called me out of the blue

703
00:42:52,600 --> 00:42:54,060
问我是不是还在查这个事
and asked me if we were still looking into it.

704
00:42:54,060 --> 00:42:55,290
所以我就查了
So I followed up.

705
00:43:00,840 --> 00:43:02,630
你偷看了我的笔记
You looked through my notes.

706
00:43:09,390 --> 00:43:10,450
滚
You're out.

707
00:43:12,320 --> 00:43:14,540
-什么  -你被开除了  杰弗瑞斯
- What? - You're fired, Jeffries.

708
00:43:15,470 --> 00:43:17,150
这是个故事  我在跟进这个故事
It's a story. I was following it.

709
00:43:17,150 --> 00:43:18,440
我不希望你跟着我干了
I don't want you on my team.

710
00:43:18,670 --> 00:43:20,100
滚出我的办公室
Get out of my office.

711
00:43:39,350 --> 00:43:41,710
我们知道我们能赢下这两个州
We know we can win both states.

712
00:43:41,720 --> 00:43:43,090
为什么不接受这个交易
Why would we not take this deal?

713
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:44,400
不  安德伍德夫妇想重新投票
No. The Underwoods want a revote

714
00:43:44,400 --> 00:43:47,040
是因为他们知道拿不下众议院  而我们能
because they know they can't win in the House. We can.

715
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:49,800
我们要做个交易  逼克莱尔·安德伍德辞职
We need to make a deal that forces Claire Underwood to resign.

716
00:43:49,800 --> 00:43:52,000
-她有那么重要吗  -我能说两句吗
- And why does that matter? - If I may?

717
00:43:52,700 --> 00:43:54,440
-议长女士  -就国会而言
- Madam Speaker. - Speaking from the Hill,

718
00:43:54,440 --> 00:43:55,750
作为副总统
as vice president,

719
00:43:55,750 --> 00:43:58,280
她可以利用这个平台公开抹黑你的所有动作
she'll have a public pulpit to discredit your every move.

720
00:43:58,280 --> 00:44:01,420
{\an3}{\pos(374,247)}美国副总统官邸

721
00:43:58,280 --> 00:44:01,420
我会把克莱尔·安德伍德流放到海军天文台I'm going to exile Claire Underwood to the Naval Observatory

722
00:44:01,420 --> 00:44:05,680
让她整天在东南亚出席国葬仪式
and stack her schedule with state funerals in Southeast Asia.

723
00:44:05,720 --> 00:44:07,300
她别想参与白宫的决策
She'll never see the inside of the West Wing,

724
00:44:07,300 --> 00:44:08,220
更别提干涉总统了
let alone the Oval.

725
00:44:08,220 --> 00:44:11,360
你需要布洛哈特在你身边支持你
You need Brockhart by your side, supporting you.

726
00:44:12,630 --> 00:44:13,810
我不想再听布洛哈特的事了
I don't want to hear about Brockhart.

727
00:44:13,810 --> 00:44:15,890
重要的是让威尔当上总统
What matters is that Will becomes president.

728
00:44:15,890 --> 00:44:18,130
安德伍德在你的政府里会造成巨大破坏的
Underwood in office can cause an enormous amount damage.

729
00:44:18,130 --> 00:44:20,620
反过来如果他们输了  他们就全完了
Whereas, if they lose, they're losers.

730
00:44:20,620 --> 00:44:23,330
我希望这场选举是在我
I want this election to be between me

731
00:44:23,780 --> 00:44:24,910
和弗兰西斯·安德伍德之间
and Francis Underwood.

732
00:44:24,910 --> 00:44:26,250
这你说了不算
Well, it isn't up to you.

733
00:44:26,310 --> 00:44:29,210
麦卡锡议长不会让这个议案进入投票的
Speaker McCarthy isn't letting this particular bill to the floor,

734
00:44:29,210 --> 00:44:30,860
除非我们附加一项修正案
unless we have an amendment attached

735
00:44:30,860 --> 00:44:32,410
将克莱尔·安德伍德赶走
that removes Claire Underwood.

736
00:44:34,670 --> 00:44:35,650
威尔
Will...

737
00:44:36,030 --> 00:44:39,710
如果你希望白宫里有位愿意合作的总统
Now, if you expect a willing partner in the White House,

738
00:44:39,710 --> 00:44:42,620
那你最好让议案原样进入表决
you'd better let that bill get to the floor as is.

739
00:44:46,580 --> 00:44:47,800
如果你坐进总统办公室  威尔
If you get to the Oval, Will,

740
00:44:47,800 --> 00:44:50,020
那时是你更需要议长  而不是反过来
you're gonna need the Speaker more than she needs you.

741
00:44:50,420 --> 00:44:51,880
我这就给她打回去
So, I'm gonna call her back,

742
00:44:52,650 --> 00:44:54,960
然后你要道歉
and you are going to apologize.

743
00:45:00,360 --> 00:45:01,320
威尔
Will.

744
00:45:04,680 --> 00:45:06,330
威尔  回来
Will, get back here!

745
00:45:07,880 --> 00:45:08,800
威尔
Will!

746
00:45:13,720 --> 00:45:14,640
别逼他了
Enough.

747
00:45:19,240 --> 00:45:20,360
关门
Shut the door.

748
00:45:31,030 --> 00:45:32,370
你看着像死人
You look like death.

749
00:45:33,800 --> 00:45:36,030
我联系不上绑匪了
I can't get in touch with the kidnappers.

750
00:45:38,370 --> 00:45:41,070
快一天了  什么消息都没有
It's been radio silence for almost 24 hours.

751
00:45:45,500 --> 00:45:47,610
有传言说他已经不在绑匪手上了
There's rumors they don't even have him anymore.

752
00:45:54,850 --> 00:45:57,310
这事我不能再瞒着总统了
I can't keep this from the president any longer.

753
00:46:01,750 --> 00:46:02,810
好吧
Okay.

754
00:46:04,020 --> 00:46:06,610
那我会告诉他你帮了好大的忙
And then I'll tell him what a big help you've been.

755
00:46:12,670 --> 00:46:15,010
再过几小时制裁就要生效了
Sanctions hit in a couple of hours.

756
00:46:15,010 --> 00:46:17,000
你要么和杜兰特国务卿谈
Deal with Secretary Durant

757
00:46:17,010 --> 00:46:19,790
要么对付几个愤怒的亿万富翁去吧
or with some very unhappy billionaires.

758
00:46:19,790 --> 00:46:24,010
你要让我在南极洲任意开采石油
You will allow me to exploit whatever oil I find in Antarctica.

759
00:46:24,220 --> 00:46:25,530
我告诉你为什么
And I'll tell you why.

760
00:46:26,120 --> 00:46:27,610
我手上有料
I have something.

761
00:46:28,060 --> 00:46:30,840
或者说有你们想要的人
Or rather, someone you need.

762
00:46:30,840 --> 00:46:32,310
你在说什么
What are you talking about?

763
00:46:32,420 --> 00:46:33,930
你们政府里有人
Someone in your administration

764
00:46:33,930 --> 00:46:37,530
愿花大钱换他平安回国
was willing to pay a great deal of money for his safe return.

765
00:46:40,160 --> 00:46:41,660
你的艾丹·麦卡伦
Your Aidan Macallan.

766
00:46:41,790 --> 00:46:44,220
他在这里  就在克里姆林宫里
He's here. In the Kremlin.

767
00:46:44,220 --> 00:46:47,510
不然你以为是谁泄的密
Who do you think orchestrated that leak?

768
00:46:47,510 --> 00:46:49,450
看来他知道的不少啊
Seems to know quite a lot.

769
00:46:49,860 --> 00:46:53,390
失陪一下  你们国务卿来了
Excuse me one moment. The Secretary of State is here.

770
00:46:53,390 --> 00:46:55,240
-国务卿女士  -先生们
- Madam Secretary. - Gentlemen.

771
00:46:55,770 --> 00:46:57,360
想必你认识艾丹吧
You must know Aidan?

772
00:46:57,360 --> 00:46:59,050
我想我不认识他
I don't believe I do.

773
00:47:03,270 --> 00:47:04,490
很高兴认识你
Nice to meet you.

774
00:47:06,040 --> 00:47:08,960
-你是美国人  -是
- You're American? - I am.

775
00:47:09,280 --> 00:47:11,840
开始会谈之前  我想让你知道
Before we begin, I'd just like you to know that

776
00:47:12,040 --> 00:47:16,690
你们的总统和前总统都在线上
the president and the former president are on the line.

777
00:47:17,670 --> 00:47:18,570
凯茜
Cathy...

778
00:47:18,570 --> 00:47:20,930
你愿意的话可以接听
You can pick up the phone, if you like.

779
00:47:25,330 --> 00:47:26,620
总统先生
Mr. President.

780
00:47:27,320 --> 00:47:29,510
你最好先回华盛顿
It's best you come back to Washington.

781
00:47:40,550 --> 00:47:41,690
有什么发现吗
Find anything yet?

782
00:47:43,100 --> 00:47:44,180
还没
Not yet.

783
00:47:45,100 --> 00:47:46,740
再次感谢  巴恩斯先生
Thank you again, Mr. Barnes,

784
00:47:46,740 --> 00:47:48,300
谢谢你让我看
for letting me take a look.

785
00:47:49,030 --> 00:47:50,060
我不会看太久
I won't be long.

786
00:47:51,160 --> 00:47:52,420
这就是全部吗
This is everything?

787
00:47:52,750 --> 00:47:55,200
这是他们从佐伊的公寓寄来的一切
This is everything they sent from Zoe's apartment.

788
00:47:57,520 --> 00:47:58,900
我就是
I just, you know...

789
00:48:00,790 --> 00:48:02,840
我不忍扔掉任何东西
I just can't seem to throw anything out.

790
00:48:07,280 --> 00:48:10,140
只是些文件  但是
I mean, it's just papers, but...

791
00:48:14,290 --> 00:48:16,900
不管怎样  你自便
Anyway, I'll leave you to it.

792
00:48:16,900 --> 00:48:19,090
-好  谢谢  -没事
- Okay. Thank you. - Yeah.

793
00:49:07,470 --> 00:49:14,020
{\an8}道格·斯坦普  瑞秋·波斯纳

794
00:49:18,100 --> 00:49:19,100
好吧
Okay.

795
00:49:23,700 --> 00:49:25,820
黑人党团  不是吧
The Black Caucus? Really?

796
00:49:25,820 --> 00:49:28,580
我喜欢马克  因为我总是知道他的立场
I like Mark, because I always know where he stands.

797
00:49:28,580 --> 00:49:30,260
通常是对人步步紧逼
It's usually on someone's neck.

798
00:49:30,260 --> 00:49:31,840
你给自己争取到了什么  一天时间吗
What did you buy yourselves, another day?

799
00:49:31,840 --> 00:49:33,870
足够跟大卫·拉斯姆森谈了
Enough time to talk to David Rasmussen,

800
00:49:33,870 --> 00:49:35,710
显然你早就跟他谈过
who you clearly spoke to before.

801
00:49:35,710 --> 00:49:37,170
然后又见了乔丹·萨多斯基
And to meet with Jordan Sadowsky

802
00:49:37,170 --> 00:49:38,770
和剩下的共和党领导人
and the rest of the Republican leadership.

803
00:49:38,770 --> 00:49:41,070
那星期二呢  星期三呢
And what happens Tuesday? Or Wednesday?

804
00:49:41,460 --> 00:49:44,080
我能让大卫和众议院
Look, I... I can have David and the House

805
00:49:44,080 --> 00:49:45,560
每次会议都对此进行投票
vote on this every single session.

806
00:49:45,560 --> 00:49:46,830
我们背景不同
Our backgrounds are different,

807
00:49:46,830 --> 00:49:49,060
但内心里我们都是穷小子
but we're both hardscrabble boys at heart.

808
00:49:49,060 --> 00:49:51,210
我们需要最后一个字  最后一击
We need the last word, last blow,

809
00:49:51,210 --> 00:49:52,410
最后一举
last move.

810
00:49:52,410 --> 00:49:54,020
我们能让众议院通过议案
We can push the bill through the House

811
00:49:54,020 --> 00:49:56,760
在田纳西州和俄亥俄州重新选举总统
for a new election for president in Tennessee and Ohio.

812
00:49:56,760 --> 00:49:58,680
麦卡锡议长不会允许那种事发生
Speaker McCarthy won't let that happen.

813
00:49:59,170 --> 00:50:02,230
但我能说服她
But I could... convince her

814
00:50:02,810 --> 00:50:04,650
如果你辞职
if you were to step down,

815
00:50:04,650 --> 00:50:06,580
我们在田纳西州和俄亥俄州
and our full tickets president and vice president

816
00:50:06,580 --> 00:50:08,870
同时进行总统和副总统的选举
run against each other in Tennessee and Ohio.

817
00:50:09,290 --> 00:50:12,390
那可不行  那可不行
Well, to hell with that. Well, to hell with that.

818
00:50:13,410 --> 00:50:17,030
我们接受交易  我想这是正确的做法
We'll make the deal. I think this is the right thing to do.

819
00:50:17,410 --> 00:50:18,500
明天我会宣布
Tomorrow, I'll announce my intention

820
00:50:18,500 --> 00:50:19,880
在重新投票后我就辞职
to step down after the revote.

821
00:50:19,880 --> 00:50:21,930
我会通知议长让议案进入投票表决
I'll let the Speaker know to put the bill on the floor.

822
00:50:22,670 --> 00:50:25,150
我们还有一件非常重要的事
We have one more outstanding piece of business,

823
00:50:25,150 --> 00:50:26,610
最高法院提名人
the Supreme Court nominee.

824
00:50:26,910 --> 00:50:29,880
我们需要任命个人来打破四四僵局
We'll need to appoint someone to break the four-four deadlock.

825
00:50:29,950 --> 00:50:31,840
批准国会的新选举日
Approve Congress' new election date.

826
00:50:31,870 --> 00:50:34,000
我们有几个人选
We, uh, have several people in mind.

827
00:50:34,000 --> 00:50:35,870
我希望你们任命伊丽莎白·本森
I want you to appoint Elizabeth Benson.

828
00:50:38,730 --> 00:50:40,630
她足够开放  你可以接受
Well, she's liberal enough for you to swallow,

829
00:50:40,770 --> 00:50:42,710
必要的时候又足够保守
and conservative enough when it counts.

830
00:50:42,710 --> 00:50:44,670
但我们没时间开参议院听证会
Yes, but we don't have time for Senate hearings.

831
00:50:44,670 --> 00:50:46,200
我可以让参议院休会
I can make a recess happen.

832
00:50:58,480 --> 00:50:59,870
竞选活动上见
I'll see you on the campaign trail.

833
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:12,860
那置我于何地  艾力克斯
Where does that leave me, huh, Alex?

834
00:51:13,360 --> 00:51:15,150
我冒了巨大风险
I went out on a limb here.

835
00:51:15,740 --> 00:51:17,940
如果我们没拿下众议院  那怎么办
If we don't have a vote in the House, then what?

836
00:51:18,090 --> 00:51:20,040
马克·厄舍是你的朋友  不是我的
Mark Usher is your friend, not mine.

837
00:51:20,040 --> 00:51:21,770
马克·厄舍不是任何人的朋友
Mark Usher's no one's friend.

838
00:51:22,300 --> 00:51:25,040
弗兰西斯·安德伍德什么也没赢  好吗
Francis Underwood hasn't won a thing, okay?

839
00:51:25,040 --> 00:51:27,630
威尔·康威有可能  很大的可能
And there's a good... More than a good chance that Will Conway

840
00:51:27,630 --> 00:51:30,210
会成为下一任美国总统
will be the next President of the United States.

841
00:52:03,500 --> 00:52:07,460
能让我单独待会儿吗  这几天太艰难了
Could you give me a moment? It's been a difficult few days.

842
00:52:12,160 --> 00:52:13,060
好点吗
Better?

843
00:52:13,450 --> 00:52:14,960
嗯
Yes.

844
00:52:16,580 --> 00:52:19,300
我们不能按原计划让众议院周一投票
We couldn't let the House vote proceed on Monday.

845
00:52:20,050 --> 00:52:21,110
为什么
Why not?

846
00:52:21,110 --> 00:52:23,100
因为你会输的
Because you would've lost.

847
00:52:24,510 --> 00:52:26,770
即使康威当了总统
Even if Conway took the presidency,

848
00:52:26,770 --> 00:52:28,480
有你  我们还是会有立足之地
we would've had a foothold with you.

849
00:52:28,480 --> 00:52:31,330
我们可以破坏他们  就像对沃克夫妇那样
We could've sabotaged, just like we did with the Walkers.

850
00:52:31,330 --> 00:52:33,350
康威夫妇不是沃克夫妇
The Conways are not the Walkers.

851
00:52:33,360 --> 00:52:36,010
那不是你能决定的
It wasn't your decision to make.

852
00:52:36,270 --> 00:52:37,430
你说什么
Excuse me?

853
00:52:37,820 --> 00:52:41,290
你自己说的  你只是代总统
You said it yourself. You're only acting.

854
00:52:49,400 --> 00:52:50,990
我赞同厄舍
I agreed with Usher

855
00:52:51,040 --> 00:52:53,580
是因为他会不惜一切
because he will sacrifice everything

856
00:52:53,580 --> 00:52:55,090
让布洛哈特上位
to get Brockhart into office,

857
00:52:55,090 --> 00:52:58,050
而这就让康威变弱  容易失败
which makes Conway weak, ready to lose.

858
00:52:58,050 --> 00:53:00,080
我以为你和我看法相同
I thought you saw what I saw.

859
00:53:01,020 --> 00:53:03,820
确实
I did. I do.

860
00:53:04,100 --> 00:53:06,630
我们完全同步  克莱尔
We're perfectly in sync, Claire.

861
00:53:27,970 --> 00:53:37,970
{\an5}{\pos(193,150)}最高法院基本任命流程是  当法院出现空缺  总统提名一个人选
然后参议院举行公开听证会  一般持续三到五天
然后参议院进行投票  如果被提名者获得多数票  就可以宣誓就职  
历史上也出现过休会任命大法官
但休会任命的局限是  在参议院复会后  还是要进行任命投票
在最高法院大法官的任命投票上  民主党在控制参议院时
取消了原有的阻挠议事  允许51票简单多数即可过关
这种规则的更改  却让共和党占了便宜
在不久前特朗普提名大法官后  因为目前共和党控制了参议院
虽然民主党非常反对  但共和党仍靠简单多数投票让大法官上任了

862
00:54:27,970 --> 00:54:37,970
{\an5}{\pos(193,150)}在美国早期  现代政党系统还没有成型的时候
出现过正副总统分属不同党派的情况
亚当斯做总统时  副总统杰斐逊跟他不是一个党派
创立了共和党的林肯  出于选举策略的考虑  选了民主党杰克逊做副总统
根据法律  这种情况是可能出现的
因为一旦选举结果有争议  需要国会来投票选举总统时
总统是由众议院选举产生  而副总统是由参议院选举产生
这就可能出现正副总统不同党  但历史上没有发生过

